parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can lead to a loss of braking ability, which can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the vehicle vibrates when braking
the ABS warning light illuminates
the traction control warning light illuminates
the check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the brakes make a grinding or vibrating noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ESC warning light illuminates
the traction control warning light illuminates
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the vehicle vibrates when driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HECU can cause an engine compartment fire, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The vehicle is at risk of catching fire while driving
and the owner is advised to park the vehicle outside and away from other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Lamp and Park Light Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lamps and park lights can increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-visibility conditions.
symptoms: The brake lamps and park lights may not function properly
and the wiring harness may overheat
causing the lamps to blow.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent malfunction of the horn can increase the risk of accidents, as the driver may not be able to alert other drivers or pedestrians in emergency situations.
symptoms: The horn may not work when needed
and the malfunction can occur randomly
without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including engine compartment fires, and can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience electrical system failures
including issues with the alternator
battery
and wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the door can cause safety issues, especially if the door opens while driving.
symptoms: The door may not open or close properly
and may even open while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to notify owners of recalls can put them at risk, as they may not be aware of potential safety issues with their vehicle.
symptoms: Owners may not receive recall notifications
or may not be aware of open recalls on their vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seat belts to properly restrain occupants can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as they are not provided with the necessary protection in a crash.
symptoms: Seat belts fail to latch or unlatch
or do not properly restrain occupants
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can lead to a failure to deploy in a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
indicating a problem with the airbag system.
